cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.CL, cs.CR

This paper focuses on characterizing a social media system, Gab, and analyzing the content shared by its users. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the moderation of content and the violation of hate speech policies, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also analyzes the dissemination of news and the reinforcement of political views, which could be related to cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
